title: Identifying risks in data
displayTitle: Identifying risks in data
body:
We have produced a set of questions to help identify data that may have risks. The FAIR data toolbox contains a guide to help identify risks in data, which includes these questions. 

First think about the sources of your data:

  • Do you have the rights to collect, access, use and share the data?
  • Is there any third party data (data owned by someone else) in the data?
  • Is there any existing ethical or legislative context you need to consider (e.g. in country and funder policies)?
  • Is the data properly described including its limitations, gaps, inconsistencies or biases?

title: The role of the foundation as a stakeholder
displayTitle: The role of the foundation as a stakeholder
body:
The foundation has a role in supporting the enabling environment by investing in initiatives aimed to help leaders and local institutions chart their own path. 

This could include investing in technical infrastructure, improving skills and knowledge and the creation of policies and processes to support FAIR and safeguarded data practices.

body:
